node.text:
Lamb Koftas with Yoghurt Dressing
(Serves 6)

Koftas are a nice alternative to the traditional burger.

1  lb/700g minced lamb
 teaspoon of ground coriander
1 teaspoon of garam masala
 teaspoon of chilli powder
 Small bunch scallions- chopped
 red chilli-finely diced
2 cloves of garlic crushed
1 tablespoon sweet chilli jam/chutney
1 egg
1 dessertspoon whole milk Natural Live natural yoghurt

Mix all ingredients together in a bowl until thoroughly combined.
If using wooden skewers soak them well before using or if not you can use metal skewers.
Roll the Koftas into long cylindrical shapes and thread them onto your desired skewers. Alternatively roll them into small meatballs and thread them onto the kebab stick, using about 4 or  5 meatballs on each stick.
It is best, where at all possible to refrigerate the mixture for at least an hour before cooking in an attempt to harden them up as if not they can have a tendency to break before cooking.

Cooking Instructions
1.	Preheat the oven to 190C/375F/Gas Mark 5)
Place the koftas in the oven for 18-20 minutes until they are cooked through. 
2.	Alternatively preheat the barbecue. Brush the Koftas with oil and cook for approximately 4-5 minutes each side on the barbecue to get a char grilled effect.

Make sure they are fully cooked through to the centre.

Yoghurt Dressing:
1 cucumber-deseeded and chopped finely
1 tablespoon whole milk Natural Live natural yoghurt
1 dessertspoon freshly chopped mint
Cracked black pepper

Mix all together and serve, well chilled.

Edward’s Handy Hints:
feel free to use some breadcrumbs in with the minced lamb to help soak up the juices of the fat whilst cooking.
